potential_causes.suggestion_localized: Practice relaxation techniques and manage workload.
potential_causes.explanation_localized: Stress and mental fatigue are common in middle-aged women and can cause frequent headaches.

potential_causes.suggestion_localized: Improve sleep hygiene, establish a relaxing bedtime routine.
potential_causes.explanation_localized: Disrupted or insufficient sleep can lead to headache episodes, especially in women over 50.

potential_causes.suggestion_localized: Take regular breaks from screens and adjust display settings.
potential_causes.explanation_localized: Extended screen use without breaks can cause eye strain and trigger headaches.

potential_causes.suggestion_localized: Maintain balanced diet and ensure adequate hydration.
potential_causes.explanation_localized: Inadequate nutrition or dehydration can contribute to headaches.

potential_causes.suggestion_localized: Monitor hormonal changes and consult a healthcare provider if needed.
potential_causes.explanation_localized: Hormonal fluctuations are common around menopause and can influence headache occurrence.

potential_causes.suggestion_localized: Practice posture correction and relaxation exercises.
potential_causes.explanation_localized: Muscle tension, especially from poor posture, can lead to tension-type headaches.

potential_causes.suggestion_localized: Reduce exposure to noisy or brightly lit environments.
potential_causes.explanation_localized: Environmental factors like noise, bright lights, or strong odors can trigger headaches in sensitive individuals.
